          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Plan Adaptation vs Full Re-Planning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a trigger fires, the most expensive response is to discard the current plan and generate a new one from scratch. Plan adaptation is the surgical alternative: modify only the affected steps while preserving the valid remainder. A well-designed adapter tries the cheapest fix first \u2014 retry, then substitute, then skip \u2014 and falls back to full re-planning only when no local repair is possible."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
