      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Data Structures"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Plan adaptation requires a mutable, indexed plan structure. The steps must be addressable by index, support insertion and deletion, and carry enough metadata for the adapter to reason about each step without re-reading context."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom enum import Enum\nfrom typing import Optional, Any\nimport anthropic\n\nclass StepStatus(Enum):\n    PENDING = \"pending\"\n    RUNNING = \"running\"\n    DONE    = \"done\"\n    FAILED  = \"failed\"\n    SKIPPED = \"skipped\"\n\n@dataclass\nclass Step:\n    id: str\n    description: str\n    tool: str             # tool name the step calls\n    tool_input: dict      # arguments to the tool\n    status: StepStatus = StepStatus.PENDING\n    result: Optional[Any] = None\n    retry_count: int = 0\n    max_retries: int = 2\n    skippable: bool = False   # can the step be omitted without breaking later steps?\n\n@dataclass\nclass AdaptivePlan:\n    goal: str\n    steps: list[Step] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n    def pending(self) -> list[Step]:\n        return [s for s in self.steps if s.status == StepStatus.PENDING]\n\n    def completed(self) -> list[Step]:\n        return [s for s in self.steps if s.status == StepStatus.DONE]\n\n    def summary(self) -> str:\n        lines = [f\"Goal: {self.goal}\"]\n        for i, s in enumerate(self.steps):\n            lines.append(f\"  [{i}] [{s.status.value}] {s.description}\")\n        return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retry Adaptation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retry is the cheapest adaptation: re-run the same step without modifying the plan. It is appropriate for transient errors \u2014 network timeouts, rate limits, tool flakiness. An exponential back-off prevents hammering a service that is temporarily overloaded."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import time\n\ndef retry_step(step: Step, execute_fn) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Returns True if the step eventually succeeded.\"\"\"\n    if step.retry_count >= step.max_retries:\n        return False\n    step.retry_count += 1\n    delay = 2 ** step.retry_count   # 2s, 4s, 8s \u2026\n    time.sleep(delay)\n    try:\n        step.result = execute_fn(step)\n        step.status = StepStatus.DONE\n        return True\n    except Exception:\n        step.status = StepStatus.FAILED\n        return False\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Substitute Adaptation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Substitution replaces a failed step with a semantically equivalent step that uses a different tool or approach. The LLM is given the failed step's description and a list of available tools, then asked to propose a substitute that achieves the same outcome."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SUBSTITUTE_PROMPT = \"\"\"A plan step has failed and cannot be retried.\nFailed step: {step_description}\nTool that was called: {tool}\nError: {error}\n\nAvailable tools: {tools}\n\nPropose a substitute step that achieves the same outcome using a different tool.\nRespond with JSON: {{\"description\": str, \"tool\": str, \"tool_input\": dict}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef substitute_step(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    plan: AdaptivePlan,\n    step_index: int,\n    error: str,\n    available_tools: list[str],\n) -> bool:\n    step = plan.steps[step_index]\n    prompt = SUBSTITUTE_PROMPT.format(\n        step_description=step.description,\n        tool=step.tool,\n        error=error,\n        tools=\", \".join(available_tools),\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    import json, re\n    raw = response.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\{.*\\}\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if not m:\n        return False\n    sub = json.loads(m.group())\n    plan.steps[step_index] = Step(\n        id=step.id + \"-sub\",\n        description=sub[\"description\"],\n        tool=sub[\"tool\"],\n        tool_input=sub[\"tool_input\"],\n        skippable=step.skippable,\n    )\n    return True\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Partial Re-Planning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When steps from index N onward depend on an assumption that is now known to be wrong, partial re-planning regenerates only the suffix of the plan starting at N. The prefix \u2014 all completed steps \u2014 is preserved. The LLM receives the current goal, the completed work, and the failure context to generate a new tail."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "PARTIAL_REPLAN_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are re-planning the tail of an in-progress agent task.\n\nGoal: {goal}\n\nCompleted steps (keep these \u2014 do NOT redo them):\n{completed_summary}\n\nThe plan was proceeding but step {failed_step} failed:\n  Description: {step_description}\n  Error: {error}\n\nGenerate the remaining steps needed to complete the goal, starting from scratch\nat the point of failure. Return JSON array of steps:\n[{{\"id\": str, \"description\": str, \"tool\": str, \"tool_input\": dict, \"skippable\": bool}}]\n\"\"\"\n\ndef partial_replan(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    plan: AdaptivePlan,\n    failed_index: int,\n    error: str,\n) -> bool:\n    completed = plan.steps[:failed_index]\n    completed_summary = \"\\n\".join(\n        f\"  - {s.description}\" for s in completed if s.status == StepStatus.DONE\n    )\n    failed_step = plan.steps[failed_index]\n    prompt = PARTIAL_REPLAN_PROMPT.format(\n        goal=plan.goal,\n        completed_summary=completed_summary or \"(none)\",\n        failed_step=failed_step.id,\n        step_description=failed_step.description,\n        error=error,\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    import json, re\n    raw = response.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\[.*\\]\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if not m:\n        return False\n    new_steps = [\n        Step(id=s[\"id\"], description=s[\"description\"],\n             tool=s[\"tool\"], tool_input=s[\"tool_input\"],\n             skippable=s.get(\"skippable\", False))\n        for s in json.loads(m.group())\n    ]\n    plan.steps = completed + new_steps\n    return True\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Unified Adapter"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A unified adapter tries each strategy in cost order and falls back to the next level only when the cheaper option fails or is inapplicable. This keeps token spend low while maximising task completion rate."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def adapt(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    plan: AdaptivePlan,\n    step_index: int,\n    error: str,\n    execute_fn,\n    available_tools: list[str],\n) -> bool:\n    step = plan.steps[step_index]\n\n    # 1. Retry (no plan change)\n    if step.retry_count < step.max_retries:\n        if retry_step(step, execute_fn):\n            return True\n\n    # 2. Substitute (local plan edit)\n    if substitute_step(client, plan, step_index, error, available_tools):\n        try:\n            s = plan.steps[step_index]\n            s.result = execute_fn(s)\n            s.status = StepStatus.DONE\n            return True\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n    # 3. Skip (if step is non-critical)\n    if step.skippable:\n        step.status = StepStatus.SKIPPED\n        return True\n\n    # 4. Partial re-plan (regenerate suffix)\n    return partial_replan(client, plan, step_index, error)\n\n\ndef run_adaptive_plan(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    plan: AdaptivePlan,\n    execute_fn,\n    available_tools: list[str],\n) -> list[Any]:\n    results = []\n    i = 0\n    while i < len(plan.steps):\n        step = plan.steps[i]\n        if step.status in (StepStatus.DONE, StepStatus.SKIPPED):\n            i += 1\n            continue\n        step.status = StepStatus.RUNNING\n        try:\n            step.result = execute_fn(step)\n            step.status = StepStatus.DONE\n            results.append(step.result)\n            i += 1\n        except Exception as e:\n            step.status = StepStatus.FAILED\n            adapted = adapt(client, plan, i, str(e), execute_fn, available_tools)\n            if not adapted:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Could not adapt step {step.id}: {e}\") from e\n            # do not increment i \u2014 re-evaluate the (possibly replaced) step\n    return results\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The loop does not increment i after a failed adaptation. The adapter either fixed the step in-place (retry/substitute) or replaced it with new steps at the same index (partial replan). Either way, re-evaluating index i is correct."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Insert Adaptation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Some failures reveal a missing prerequisite: a step needs a resource that does not exist yet because the plan assumed it would be provided. Insert adaptation injects one or more preparatory steps immediately before the blocked step."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "INSERT_PROMPT = \"\"\"A plan step is blocked because a prerequisite is missing.\nBlocked step: {step_description}\nMissing prerequisite: {prerequisite}\nAvailable tools: {tools}\n\nReturn a JSON array of steps to obtain the prerequisite:\n[{{\"id\": str, \"description\": str, \"tool\": str, \"tool_input\": dict}}]\n\"\"\"\n\ndef insert_prerequisite(\n    client: anthropic.Anthropic,\n    plan: AdaptivePlan,\n    step_index: int,\n    prerequisite: str,\n    available_tools: list[str],\n) -> bool:\n    step = plan.steps[step_index]\n    prompt = INSERT_PROMPT.format(\n        step_description=step.description,\n        prerequisite=prerequisite,\n        tools=\", \".join(available_tools),\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        messages=[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":prompt}],\n    )\n    import json, re\n    raw = response.content[0].text\n    m = re.search(r\"\\[.*\\]\", raw, re.DOTALL)\n    if not m:\n        return False\n    new_steps = [\n        Step(id=s[\"id\"], description=s[\"description\"],\n             tool=s[\"tool\"], tool_input=s[\"tool_input\"])\n        for s in json.loads(m.group())\n    ]\n    plan.steps[step_index:step_index] = new_steps\n    return True\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Plan adaptation modifies an existing plan surgically rather than discarding it; preserved steps represent computation already completed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Strategy cost order: retry (no change) \u2192 substitute (one step replaced) \u2192 skip (step removed) \u2192 partial re-plan (suffix regenerated) \u2192 full re-plan."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A unified adapter tries each strategy in cost order; the loop re-evaluates the same index after any adaptation."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Partial re-planning uses completed steps as context for the LLM, preventing regression to already-done work."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Insert adaptation handles missing prerequisites by injecting new steps without touching the rest of the plan."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Marking steps skippable at plan-creation time lets the adapter skip non-critical steps without an LLM call."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}